{
  "lesson_number": 12,
  "title": "Lesson 12",
  "topic": "Verb conjugation - Present tense",
  "grammar": {
    "explanations": [
      "So far only the present tense, active voice, third person singular and plural have been introduced. This lesson gives the conjugation in full.",
      "The present tense active voice is conjugated as follows. In the singular: third person (So) pacati = He cooks; second person (Tvaṃ) pacasi = You cook; first person (Ahaṃ) pacāmi = I cook. In the plural: third person (Te) pacanti = They cook; second person (Tumhe) pacatha = You cook; first person (Mayaṃ) pacāma = We cook."
    ],
    "tables": [
      {
        "title": "Present Tense, Active Voice - pacati (to cook)",
        "rows": [
          [
            "Person",
            "Singular",
            "Plural"
          ],
          [
            "3rd",
            "(So) pacati = He cooks",
            "(Te) pacanti = They cook"
          ],
          [
            "2nd",
            "(Tvaṃ) pacasi = You cook",
            "(Tumhe) pacatha = You cook"
          ],
          [
            "1st",
            "(Ahaṃ) pacāmi = I cook",
            "(Mayaṃ) pacāma = We cook"
          ]
        ]
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "pali": "So bhattaṃ pacati",
        "english": "He cooks rice."
      },
      {
        "pali": "Tvaṃ bhattaṃ pacasi",
        "english": "You (sg.) cook rice."
      },
      {
        "pali": "Ahaṃ bhattaṃ pacāmi",
        "english": "I cook rice."
      },
      {
        "pali": "Te bhattaṃ pacanti",
        "english": "They cook rice."
      },
      {
        "pali": "Tumhe bhattaṃ pacatha",
        "english": "You (pl.) cook rice."
      },
      {
        "pali": "Mayaṃ bhattaṃ pacāma",
        "english": "We cook rice."
      }
    ]
  },
